page.title: 01INTRODUCTION TO KEYINGHAM
page.content: This area encloses two villages Keyingham and Ottringham, both dating back before the original Domesday book of 1086. Both villages are relatively undeveloped although being situated on a very busy East Coast road between the city of Hull and the mainly tourist resort of Withernsea. Nestling amid some of the most agriculturally productive land of Holderness, these two villages are regarded as country backwaters by town inhabitants, whereas in reality they are pleasant friendly places with a great sense of community spirit, a haven from the 'rat race' of city life.
